<br>
Of course it is easy to buy the trilogy now which provides you the needed CD code.<br>
<br>
Changing accounts is a function at the start up screen. When you hit log in, you simply type in manually the account name and the password for that account to activate that account.<br>
<br>
You can play EQ on ANY computer that has the cds installed, all you need is to log in on an active account and have the area you are in loaded to that computer.<br>
<br>
When you log out, the next time you log in on that computer it will list the account name of the account that was last logged into. If you want a to play a different account just click on the account name and use backspace to clear the area and then type in the appropriate account name. Make sure you use the correct password for the account name to log in.<br>
<br>
2 people CAN NOT play on a single account at the same physical time. No matter how many computers you have.<br>
<br>
Your hotkeys and such are stored on the computer, so you will have to set them up each time you play on a new computer the first time. Same with friends lists and ignore lists. And of course the screen settings are based on what the computer you are playing on are set at. Same with chat screen colors for the different messages. Ect Ect....... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxeshofsharvahl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>XeshofSharVahl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/8/02 12:58:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Valquiss, please enlighten me, Kromus.</span><hr size=1> /camp server will take you to the server selection screen. Hitting Esc will take you to the login screen.<br>
